Queensland toddler Kyhesha-Lee Joughin was forced to use the room she was locked in as a toilet before dying in severe distress of internal injuries , a court has heard on Wednesday as family friend who was charged with the toddlers manslaughter was granted bail .
The bail hearing revealed that Kyhes-Lee suffered blows to her stomach causing severe bowel damage - ultimately leading to her death .
Her father Matthew Lee Williamson and Christopher Arthur Neville Kent have both been charged with manslaughter and child cruelty .